{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CA5HFXG2pipm5kSb8xdg1e","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The kubectl log only shows the verbs (GET/POST/PATCH), not actual command lines. This makes sense since this is the proxy log. The precondition didn't seem to make any changes - it was just a probe check that `kubectl get pods -n spark-skew | grep -c Running` returned 2.\n\nLet me now look at whether there's any evidence in the run structure that suggests the precondition applied something before this stage. The precondition.log only showed:\n```\n[precondition:spark_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'spark_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n spark-skew get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n```\n\nThis is just a probe - it only checks. No apply step modified anything. So the Spark jobs were already deployed and running when this stage started.\n\nThis means the question says \"diagnose and fix bugs that prevent jobs from running\" but the jobs appear to already be running. The key insight is that the `skew-scripts` ConfigMap contains a placeholder `run_skew.sh` that doesn't actually run Spark - the actual jobs bypass this entirely by embedding their scripts inline as base64. Since all 3 jobs completed successfully, I need to document what I've found.\n\nThe real bug is that placeholder ConfigMap, even though the deployments don't reference it. Let me verify whether anything actually uses it before deciding how to fix it.\n```","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":542,"cache_read_input_tokens":74908,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":542},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2adf6e87-170c-4611-8806-dd7cfe013ba7","uuid":"977d658e-53a9-4984-8a7d-